7 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 17, Chapter 101, Subchapter 1, is
8 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
9 17-101-104. Veterinary telemedicine standards.
10 (a) Only a licensed veterinarian shall provide veterinary telemedicine
11 to an animal patient located in this state.
12 (b) In an emergency or urgent situation, a licensed veterinarian may
13 provide veterinary telemedicine without previously establishing a
14 veterinarian-client-patient relationship if the licensed veterinarian
15 establishes a veterinarian-client-patient relationship within:
16 (1) Seven (7) calendar days after providing the veterinary
17 telemedicine services for a small animal; or
18 (2) Twenty-one (21) calendar days after providing the veterinary
19 telemedicine services for a large animal.
